14/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The need for signing a bilateral agreement on protecting classified information was among the issues discussed on the first day of Croatian Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic's visit to Bulgaria Monday (13 September). Roncevic met with Bulgarian counterpart, Nikolay Svinarov, for talks on bilateral co-operation in the defence and security sectors, Euro-Atlantic integration and the fight against international terrorism. During the meeting, Svinarov reaffirmed Bulgarian support for Croatia's NATO membership bid. (BNT - 14/09/04)
